    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine, characterized by its individual throttle bodies and high-pressure dual VANOS variable valve timing. This naturally aspirated powerplant is mated to a Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a limited-slip M-differential, providing an unfiltered analog connection to the road. The chassis remains composed with aluminum control arms and a multi-link rear suspension; notably, the rear subframe has been reinforced to mitigate common fatigue points. The engine exhibits strong compression across all cylinders, and the cooling system has been refreshed with an aluminum radiator. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with enthusiast use, the mechanical vital signs are robust, making this an ideal candidate for those who prioritize driving dynamics and engineering purity.",
      "price": 34500.0,
      "reputation": 0.7,
